1. The crocodile was sighted in the Boyne River, not south of the Boyne River
2. Estimated to be about 2 metres in length;
3. Mr. Meehan is certain he wouldn't mistake a croc. He has seen them many times in the wild during many holiday trips to the Cape and to Darwin. He has been a regular visitor to croc farms, both at Rockhampton and Darwin, and has tagged croc skulls, which he purchased at the farms, at home on display.
